            <title>[KAFKA-985] Increasing log retention quickly overflows scala Int</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-985</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After increasing log.retention.hours from the default of 168 to 744 (31 days) I noticed that logs were being deleted at every cleanup interval.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;scala&amp;gt; val retentionMs: Long = 60 * 60 * 1000 * 31 * 24&lt;br/&gt;
retentionMs: Long = -1616567296&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This only appears to affect trunk.  I&apos;ll attach the minor patch I&apos;m using locally.  Thanks.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
